The paper focuses on the staffing of a teleoperations system for autonomous vehicles, which involves both human expertise and automated systems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of artificial intelligence systems in the teleoperations process, which suggests that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also addresses issues related to reliability and safety, which are relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper's methodology may be of use in other applications that combine human expertise and automated systems, which suggests that it may also belong to the Cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-category.
